      • getTitleFromStringValue

        public static java.lang.String getTitleFromStringValue​(java.lang.String selectName,
                                                       java.lang.String value)
        Method to search title corresponding to a couple (selectName / value) when it is sure that there is a match. Otherwise prefer using getOptionalTitleFromStringValue(String, String).
        Parameters:
        selectName - : String representing the name of a string selection.
        value - : String representing the value among the possible ones from to selection named by selectName.
        Returns:
        the String corresponding to the label as displayed (before translation) in views corresponding to given couple (selectName & value). Can be null if no title is associated to the found selection option.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the couple (selectName / value) doesn't match any existing selection.
